div.p: Each tax extraction point connects to a point of sovereignty. Sometimes the business is on the master side of the contractual relation, other times the slave. Hence relationships are determined by roles within a territorial landscape, rather than disconnected identities. So for outputs and labour the business is sovereign over customers and employees; but for profits and inputs, state or supplier are sovereign. It is easy to see, therefore, how the consequences of Unitary Interface Projection permeate every level of the commercial landscape.
